> 5. **"Sam and the Tigers: A New Telling of Little Black Sambo" by Julius Lester**: Without the racial bias of the original story, this retelling introduces a boy named Sam who outwits several tigers (the 'bad guys') and turns them into butter for his pancakes!
> 
> Remember, reading these books with your son provides a great opportunity to discuss 'bad guys', scary things, and more importantly, how the characters in the stories manage these situations. It's a way to reassure and help children understand that scary things can be confronted and overcome.
